I dont agree with all their methods but I dont rant about them either cause they are as good and rightious as mine.<br>
<br>
<br>
 - Baldrik<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubarshproudgut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BarshProudgut</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/31/01 11:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=156>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Real People</span><hr size=1> Well, last night as the events were unfolding I was angry and had a lot of opinions.<br>
<br>
I wondered how someone could knowingly and purposefully ruin another guild’s raid in the pursuit of loot? What kind of person is so loot-frenzied and self-serving as to trample over the other people who play this game? I honestly couldn’t believe it was happening. Surely the IV people sitting at their keyboards knew that they would sour the experience and crush the emotions of 50 other people sitting behind their keyboards? <br>
<br>
PO was in Fear. Half the zone was already cleared when the servers crashed. We knew that IV would want Cazic, but we had the zone. We were there first, doing our thing, and we were not in any way threatening the spawn claimed by them. We offered to clear a path to the god for them. The problem is, though, that we cannot clear as fast as they can.<br>
<br>
So, to save themselves a little bit of time to rush to an uncontested spawn, a decision was made by every IV member who zoned into Fear to ruin the night for a large number of people. Their justification: phat lewtz.<br>
<br>
Why have a moral compass when you have absolute power? IV isn’t breaking any game rules, after all.<br>
<br>
Then I spoke to an IV person in chat room tells. At the time, I thought to myself that she was trying to defend the indefensible. Here are her arguments:<br>
<br>
It’s getting late and some people from IV had to go to bed. She said that Fear needed to be cleared at IV pace to sustain the troops necessary to kill Cazic. If IV failed to kill Cazic, she feared that CC would grab him in the morning. The high-end game is about competition. After all, IV offered to kill everything in the zone and give PO all looting rights. PO is the one being unreasonable. This is how it’s done on other servers.<br>
<br>
And then it dawned on me. It really is all about the loot. No other thing was factored into the decision-making process, it’s all about the loot. I confess that I’m a noob. This is my first character to reach level 55, and my first foray into the high-end game. I stupidly imagined that the considerate, polite relations I’ve enjoyed with other guilds to date would continue beyond level 55. The high-end game – as played by IV – is a Quake-style competition against other people. The challenge is in defeating mobs, and in beating the competition who want to fight the same mobs.<br>
<br>
So, the bottom line is that IV will do whatever it must in pursuit of its own interests. Everyone else who plays the game either needs to conform or get the hell out of the way. That’s fine, I respect that now that I understand it. Just don’t deny that this is your stance when, in another situation, a different stance would suit you better.<br>
<br>
Back when I was innocent and foolish, I believed that it was an unfathomable breech of decency to enter a camped plane and slaughter mobs from under the noses of those there first. I’ve been told that this is not the lowest you can go, either. This happens on other servers with regularity. In fact.. isn’t that why many of us came to Vazaelle in the first place? To escape the very thing that’s become the norm here? If you wanted to make Vazaelle into Nameless_02, I wish you would have stated so earlier.<br>
<br>
Okay, so sorry I complained and whined. I didn’t understand the rules of the high-end game, thanks for making it clear. No one has to be nice anymore when loot is in the balance.<br>
<br>
I have friends in IV, and I have no enemies there that I know of. My friends are still my friends I hope despite my rant, and I sure don’t need any enemies. IV will do whatever it needs to do to advance its agenda. I will do my best to stay out of your way.<br>
<br>
No longer a complainer, now simply disillusioned.<br>
<br>
Regards <br>
