<br>
Lanys doesn't represent all of EQ, but let's look at some of its history.<br>
<br>
Last fall, the three largest guilds were Soul Assassins, Circle of Truth, and Inner Fire.<br>
<br>
SA was a lot like IV, and played with the same competitive fire.  IF and CoT resented this, because it inhibited them, and sometimes prevented them from what they wanted to do -- SA took all gods, would kill Trak and VS before other guilds could get an opportunity.<br>
<br>
Anyway, fast forward a couple of months, and SA is now called Conquest.  CoT has disbanded, and many of CoT's core members are in Conquest.  Fast forward another few months, and CQ has been disbanded by Verant for exploiting, and most of the members quit EQ because they disagreed.  A new guild was formed, with most of its members coming from the recently disbanded IF, people who opening disputed CQ's techniques.  The new guild is called Visions, and plays very much like CQ, with most of the same policies, doing things that they once preached against, because they are now in the position to do so.  Another guild which preached against SA but had less power at the time, Seven Dreams, is also playing as SA did, now that they have a monopoly on Trak with Visions mostly uninterested.<br>
<br>
There are people like Zozz who are people of principle and believe what they believe, no matter what guild they're in.  Actually, I left Lanys because I didn't agree with how hostile my guild, CoT, was towards SA.  I respected their rights and defended them. <br>
<br>
However, this is just a game, and most people can forgive themselves for having shifting morals.  History shows -- and not just on Lanys -- that people play and promote systems that benefit themselves, and do change policies as their situation/capabilities change. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uxxragincajunxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xX Ragin Cajun Xx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/31/01 12:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=160>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Real People</span><hr size=1> Ceros your right the calander is not the point, it was an example of what is going on. I think Barsh covered the topic rather precisely.<br>
